pr-worktree-rm-merged-closed [--yes|-y] [--dry-run|-n]

Automatically delete every git worktree in the current repo whose
branch has a GitHub PR that is already merged or closed.

Builds the same branch -> pr_state map that pr-worktree-rm uses
(`gh pr list --state all --limit 500 --json number,state,headRefName`),
walks `git worktree list --porcelain`, and selects every worktree
whose branch resolves to a PR in state `merged` or `closed`. The
current worktree and the main/primary worktree are always excluded.

Worktrees with `pr-status = no-pr` (no PR ever opened for the branch)
or `pr-status = open` are LEFT ALONE — this function only acts on PRs
that have reached a terminal state. Use pr-worktree-rm for the
interactive picker that can also remove no-pr / open worktrees.

Each worktree is removed with `git worktree remove`; on failure it
retries with `--force` (uncommitted changes in a worktree whose PR
has already landed are nearly always stale rebase/merge debris).
`git worktree prune` runs once at the end.

Flags:
  --yes, -y       Skip the confirmation prompt (for cron / scripts).
  --dry-run, -n   List the worktrees that would be deleted and exit 0.

Requires: gh, git, jq.
